WEBVTT

00:21.600 --> 00:22.240
CONCLUSION.

00:24.120 --> 00:27.720
To the sick the doctors wisely recommend a change of air and scenery.

00:28.520 --> 00:34.640
Thank heaven here is not all the world. The buckeye does not grow in New England,

00:34.880 --> 00:41.680
and the mockingbird is rarely heard here. The wild goose is more of a cosmopolite than we.

00:42.960 --> 00:47.300
He breaks his fast in Canada, takes a luncheon in the Ohio,

00:48.060 --> 00:54.620
and plumes himself for the night in a southern bayou. Even the bison, to some extent,

00:54.620 --> 01:00.240
keeps pace with the seasons, cropping the pastures of the Colorado only till a greener

01:00.240 --> 01:06.820
and sweeter grass awaits him by the Yellowstone. Yet we think that if rail fences are pulled down

01:06.820 --> 01:15.960
and stone walls piled up on our farms, bounds are henceforth set to our lives and our fates decided.

01:16.400 --> 01:22.380
If you are chosen town clerk forsooth, you cannot go to Tierra del Fuego this summer,

01:22.380 --> 01:29.280
but you may go to the land of infernal fire nevertheless. The universe is wider than our

01:29.280 --> 01:37.920
views of it. Yet we should oftener look over the tafferal of our craft, like curious passengers,

01:38.900 --> 01:46.300
and not make the voyage like stupid sailors picking oakum. The other side of the globe

01:46.300 --> 01:53.560
is but the home of our correspondent. Our voyaging is only great circle sailing,

01:54.160 --> 02:00.320
and the doctors prescribe for diseases of the skin merely. One hastens to southern Africa to

02:00.320 --> 02:08.600
chase the giraffe. But surely that is not the game he would be after. How long prey would a

02:08.600 --> 02:14.920
man hunt giraffes if he could? Snipes and woodcocks also may afford rare sport,

02:15.780 --> 02:23.560
but I trust it would be nobler game to shoot one's self. Direct your eye inward,

02:23.920 --> 02:33.320
and you'll find a thousand regions in your mind yet undiscovered. Travel them, and be expert in

02:33.320 --> 02:35.620
home cosmography.

02:37.400 --> 02:48.680
What does Africa, what does the West, stand for? Is not our own interior white on the chart,

02:49.300 --> 02:57.200
black though it may prove, like the coast when discovered? Is it the source of the Nile or the

02:57.820 --> 03:05.260
Mississippi or a northwest passage around this continent that we would find? Are these the

03:05.260 --> 03:14.240
problems which most concern mankind? Is Franklin the only man who is lost that his wife should be

03:14.240 --> 03:24.420
so earnest to find him? Does Mr. Grinnell know where he himself is? Be rather the Mongo Park,

03:24.420 --> 03:33.660
the Lewis and Clark and Frobisher of your own streams and oceans. Explore your own higher

03:33.660 --> 03:42.080
latitudes with shiploads of preserved meats to support you, if they be necessary, and pile the

03:42.080 --> 03:52.940
empty cans sky-high for a sign. Were preserved meats invented to preserve meat merely? Nay,

03:53.540 --> 04:04.580
be a Columbus to whole new continents and worlds within you, opening new channels, not of trade,

04:05.740 --> 04:14.600
but of thought. Every man is the lord of a realm beside which the earthly empire of the Tsar,

04:14.600 --> 04:22.900
a hummock left by the ice. Yet some can be patriotic who have no self-respect

04:23.460 --> 04:30.200
and sacrifice the greater to the less. They love the soil which makes their graves,

04:30.900 --> 04:36.060
but have no sympathy with the spirit which may still animate their clay.

04:37.760 --> 04:45.660
Patriotism is a maggot in their heads. What was the meaning of that South Sea exploring expedition

04:45.660 --> 04:52.180
with all its parade and expense, but an indirect recognition of the fact that there are continents

04:52.180 --> 05:01.980
and seas in the moral world to which every man is an isthmus or an inlet, yet unexplored by him,

05:01.980 --> 05:08.340
but that it is easier to sail many thousand miles through cold and storm and cannibals

05:08.340 --> 05:13.560
in a government ship, with five hundred men and boys to assist one,

05:14.420 --> 05:22.940
than it is to explore the private sea, the Atlantic and Pacific Ocean, of one's being alone.

05:32.120 --> 05:42.220
Habit hic vitae plus habit il vie. Let them wander and scrutinize the outlandish Australians.

05:43.100 --> 05:50.720
I have more of God, they more of the road. It is not worth the while to go round the world

05:50.720 --> 05:57.320
to count the cats in Zanzibar. Yet do this even till you can do better,

05:58.060 --> 06:08.680
and you may perhaps find some sims whole by which to get at the inside at last. England and France,

06:09.680 --> 06:20.320
Spain and Portugal, Gold Coast and Slave Coast, all front on this private sea. But no bark from

06:20.320 --> 06:26.120
them has ventured out of sight of land, though it is without doubt the direct way to India.

06:26.120 --> 06:31.720
If you would learn to speak all tongues, and conform to the customs of all nations,

06:31.760 --> 06:39.420
if you would travel farther than all travellers, be naturalized in all climes, and cause the sphinx

06:39.420 --> 06:48.000
to dash her head against a stone, even obey the precept of the old philosopher, and explore

06:48.000 --> 06:56.180
thyself. Herein are demanded the eye and the nerve. Only the defeated and deserters go to

06:56.180 --> 07:04.920
the wars, cowards that run away and enlist. Start now on that farthest western way,

07:05.440 --> 07:10.040
which does not pause at the Mississippi or the Pacific, nor conduct toward a worn-out

07:10.040 --> 07:19.680
China or Japan, but leads on direct, a tangent to this sphere, summer and winter, day and night,

07:19.800 --> 07:29.780
sun down, moon down, and at last earth down too. It is said that Mirabeau took to highway robbery

07:30.360 --> 07:35.440
to ascertain what degree of resolution was necessary in order to place oneself in formal

07:35.440 --> 07:43.060
opposition to the most sacred laws of society. He declared that a soldier who fights in the ranks

07:43.060 --> 07:49.700
does not require half so much courage as a foot-pat, that honor and religion have never

07:49.700 --> 07:56.680
stood in the way of a well-considered and a firm resolve. This was manly as the world goes,

07:57.160 --> 08:04.220
and yet it was idle, if not desperate. A saner man would have found himself often enough

08:04.220 --> 08:11.200
in formal opposition to what are deemed the most sacred laws of society,

08:12.000 --> 08:18.320
through obedience to yet more sacred laws, and so have tested his resolution without going out

08:18.320 --> 08:24.880
of his way. It is not for a man to put himself in such an attitude to society, but to maintain

08:24.880 --> 08:30.960
himself in whatever attitude he find himself through obedience to the laws of his being,

08:31.520 --> 08:37.700
which will never be one of opposition to a just government, if he should chance to meet with such.

08:38.460 --> 08:45.140
I left the woods for as good a reason as I went there. Perhaps it seemed to me that I had several

08:45.140 --> 08:53.200
more lives to live, and could not spare any more time for that one. It is remarkable how easily

08:53.200 --> 08:59.540
and insensibly we fall into a particular route and make a beaten track for ourselves.

09:00.180 --> 09:04.740
I had not lived there a week before my feet wore a path from my door to the pond side,

09:05.400 --> 09:12.740
and though it is five or six years since I trod it, it is still quite distinct. It is true,

09:12.800 --> 09:19.580
I fear, that others may have fallen into it, and so help to keep it open. The surface of the earth

09:19.580 --> 09:27.340
is soft and impressible by the feet of men, and so with the paths which the mind travels.

09:28.260 --> 09:37.220
How worn and dusty, then, must be the highways of the world, how deep the ruts of tradition

09:37.220 --> 09:47.820
and conformity! I did not wish to take a cabin passage, but rather to go before the mast and on

09:47.820 --> 09:54.880
the deck of the world, for there I could best see the moonlight amid the mountains.

09:55.900 --> 10:04.940
I do not wish to go below now. I learned this, at least, by my experiment, that if one advances

10:04.940 --> 10:11.400
confidently in the direction of his dreams, and endeavors to live the life which he has imagined,

10:12.580 --> 10:20.600
he will meet with a success unexpected in common hours. He will put some things behind,

10:21.140 --> 10:31.320
will pass an invisible boundary, new universal and more liberal laws will begin to establish

10:31.320 --> 10:37.740
themselves around and within him, or the old laws be expanded and interpreted in his favor

10:37.740 --> 10:47.340
in a more liberal sense, and he will live with the license of a higher order of beings.

10:48.300 --> 10:53.120
In proportion, as he simplifies his life, the laws of the universe will appear

10:53.120 --> 11:02.520
less complex, and solitude will not be solitude, nor poverty poverty, nor weakness weakness.

11:03.440 --> 11:12.560
If you have built castles in the air, your work need not be lost. That is where they should be.

11:13.160 --> 11:20.780
Now put the foundations under them. It is a ridiculous demand which England and America make

11:20.780 --> 11:28.380
that you shall speak so that they can understand you. Neither men nor toadstools grow so,

11:29.060 --> 11:33.700
as if that were important, and there were not enough to understand you without them,

11:34.580 --> 11:41.920
as if nature could support but one order of understandings, could not sustain birds

11:41.920 --> 11:48.090
as well as quadrupeds, flying as well as creeping things, and hush and woe,

11:49.220 --> 11:57.840
which Bright can understand, were the best English, as if there were safety in stupidity alone.

11:58.720 --> 12:05.160
I fear chiefly lest my expression may not be extravagant enough, may not wander far enough

12:05.160 --> 12:13.640
beyond the narrow limits of my daily experience, so as to be adequate to the truth of which I have

12:13.640 --> 12:24.700
been convinced. Extravagance. It depends on how you are yarded. The migrating buffalo which

12:24.700 --> 12:32.820
seeks new pastures in another latitude is not extravagant, like the cow which kicks over the

12:32.820 --> 12:40.480
hill, leaps the cow-yard fence, and runs after her calf in milking-time. I desire to speak

12:40.480 --> 12:49.780
somewhere without bounds, like a man in a waking moment, to men in their waking moments,

12:50.760 --> 12:59.900
for I am convinced that I cannot exaggerate enough even to lay the foundation of a true

12:59.900 --> 13:09.460
expression. Who that has heard a strain of music feared then lest he should speak extravagantly

13:09.460 --> 13:19.760
any more for ever, in view of the future or possible? We should live quite laxly and undefined

13:19.760 --> 13:30.640
front, our outlines dim and misty on that side, as our shadows reveal an insensible perspiration

13:31.200 --> 13:40.180
toward the sun. The volatile truth of our words should continually betray the inadequacy

13:40.180 --> 13:48.480
of the residual statement. Their truth is instantly translated. Its literal monument

13:48.480 --> 13:59.380
alone remains. The words which express our faith and piety are not definite, yet they are significant

13:59.380 --> 14:09.660
and fragrant, like frankincense to superior natures. Why level downward to our dullest

14:09.660 --> 14:18.780
perception always, and praise that as common sense? The commonest sense is the sense of men

14:18.780 --> 14:28.800
asleep, which they express by snoring. Sometimes we are inclined to class those who are once and a

14:28.800 --> 14:35.600
half witted with a half witted, because we appreciate only a third part of their wit.

14:36.400 --> 14:42.840
Some would find fault with the morning red, if they ever got up early enough. They pretend,

14:42.840 --> 14:51.000
as I hear, that the verses of Kabir have four different senses—illusion, spirit, intellect,

14:51.320 --> 14:57.660
and the exoteric doctrine of the Vedas. But in this part of the world it is considered a ground

14:57.660 --> 15:03.280
for complaint if a man's writings admit of more than one interpretation, while England endeavors

15:03.280 --> 15:14.660
to cure the potato rot. Will not any endeavor to cure the brain rot, which prevails so much more

15:14.660 --> 15:22.380
widely and fatally? I do not suppose that I have attained to obscurity, but I should be proud if

15:22.380 --> 15:28.720
no more fatal fault were found with my pages on this score than was found with the Walden ice.

15:29.440 --> 15:35.060
Southern customers objected to its blue color, which is the evidence of its purity,

15:35.680 --> 15:41.360
as if it were muddy, and preferred the Cambridge ice, which is white, but tastes of weeds.

15:43.000 --> 15:50.920
The purity men love is like the mists which envelop the earth, and not like the azure ether

15:50.920 --> 15:59.820
beyond. Some are dinning in our ears that we Americans, and moderns generally, are intellectual

15:59.820 --> 16:07.560
dwarves compared with the ancients, or even the Elizabethan men. But what is that to the purpose?

16:08.040 --> 16:15.280
A living dog is better than a dead lion. Shall a man go and hang himself because he belongs to the

16:15.280 --> 16:21.680
race of pygmies, and not be the biggest pygmy that he can? Let everyone mind his own business,

16:22.620 --> 16:29.680
and endeavor to be what he was made. Why should we be in such a desperate haste

16:29.680 --> 16:37.320
to succeed, and in such desperate enterprises? If a man does not keep pace with his companions,

16:38.140 --> 16:46.340
perhaps it is because he hears a different drummer. Let him step to the music which he hears,

16:46.880 --> 16:55.120
however measured or far away. It is not important that he should mature as soon as an apple tree or

16:55.120 --> 17:03.680
an oak. Shall he turn his spring into summer? If the condition of things which we were made for

17:03.680 --> 17:12.880
is not yet, what were any reality which we can substitute? We will not be shipwrecked on a vain

17:12.880 --> 17:22.560
reality. Shall we with pains erect a heaven of blue glass over ourselves, though when it is done

17:22.560 --> 17:30.400
we shall be sure to gaze still at the true ethereal heaven, far above, as if the former were not?

17:31.100 --> 17:37.900
There was an artist in the city of Coru who was disposed to strive after perfection.

17:38.860 --> 17:45.740
One day it came into his mind to make a staff. Having considered that in an imperfect work

17:45.740 --> 17:52.480
time is an ingredient, but in a perfect work time does not enter, he said to himself,

17:52.740 --> 17:58.480
it shall be perfect in all respects, though I should do nothing else in my life.

17:59.060 --> 18:04.960
He proceeded instantly to the forest for wood, being resolved that it should not be made of

18:04.960 --> 18:10.740
unsuitable material, and as he searched for and rejected stick after stick, his friends

18:10.740 --> 18:18.980
gradually deserted him, for they grew old in their works and died. But he grew not older by a moment.

18:20.040 --> 18:28.320
His singleness of purpose and resolution and his elevated piety endowed him without his knowledge.

18:28.480 --> 18:35.720
With perennial youth, as he made no compromise with time, time kept out of his way,

18:36.060 --> 18:42.280
and only sighed at a distance because he could not overcome him. Before he had found a stock

18:42.280 --> 18:50.280
in all respects suitable, the city of Coru was a hoary ruin, and he sat on one of its mounds

18:50.280 --> 18:56.640
to peel the stick. Before he had given it the proper shape, the dynasty of the Kandahars

18:56.640 --> 19:03.860
was at an end, and with the point of the stick he wrote the name of the last of that race in the sand,

19:04.700 --> 19:11.060
and then resumed his work. By the time he had smoothed and polished the staff,

19:11.740 --> 19:19.880
Kalpa was no longer the pole star, and ere he had put on the ferul and the head adorned with

19:19.880 --> 19:25.860
stones Brahma had awoke and slumbered many times.

19:27.040 --> 19:33.860
But why do I stay to mention these things? When the finishing stroke was put to his work,

19:35.000 --> 19:49.860
it suddenly expanded before the eyes of the astonished artist into the fairest of all the

19:49.860 --> 19:58.280
a world with full and fair proportions, in which, though the old cities and dynasties had passed

19:58.280 --> 20:06.260
away, fairer and more glorious ones had taken their place, and now he saw by the heap of shavings

20:06.260 --> 20:15.120
still fresh at his feet, that for him and his work the former lapse of time had been an illusion,

20:15.120 --> 20:21.480
and that no more time had elapsed than is required for a single scintillation of the

20:21.480 --> 20:29.120
brain of Brahma to fall on and inflame the tinder of a mortal brain. The material was pure,

20:29.320 --> 20:38.780
and his art was pure. How could the result be other than wonderful? No face which we give to

20:38.780 --> 20:49.420
matter will stead us so well at last as the truth. This alone wears well. For the most part we are

20:49.420 --> 20:58.820
not where we are, but in a false position. Through an infinity of our natures we suppose a case and

20:58.820 --> 21:05.780
put ourselves into it, and hence are in two cases at the same time, and it is doubly difficult to

21:05.780 --> 21:15.460
get out. In sane moments we regard only the facts, the case, that is. Say what you have to say,

21:16.280 --> 21:24.420
not what you ought. Any truth is better than make-believe. Tom Hyde, at the tinker,

21:24.900 --> 21:27.820
standing on the gallows, was asked if he had anything to say.

21:28.920 --> 21:31.480
"'Tell the tailors,' said he,

21:31.660 --> 21:36.460
to remember to make a knot in their thread before they take the first stitch.

21:37.860 --> 21:44.980
His companion's prayer is forgotten. However mean your life is, meet it

21:45.760 --> 21:53.920
and live it. Do not shun it and call it hard names. It is not so bad as you are.

21:54.750 --> 22:03.240
It looks poorest when you are richest. The fault-finder will find faults even in paradise.

22:04.760 --> 22:13.640
Love your life, poor as it is. You may perhaps have some pleasant, thrilling, glorious hours,

22:14.260 --> 22:21.700
even in a poor house. The setting sun is reflected from the windows of the almshouse

22:21.700 --> 22:30.560
as brightly as from the rich man's abode. The snow melts before its door as early in the spring.

22:32.080 --> 22:40.420
I do not see but a quiet mind may live as contentedly there and have as cheering thoughts

22:41.100 --> 22:48.940
as in a palace. The town's poor seem to me often to live the most independent lives of any.

22:50.180 --> 22:58.240
Maybe they are simply great enough to receive without misgiving. Most think that they are above

22:58.240 --> 23:04.160
being supported by the town, but it oftener happens that they are not above supporting

23:04.160 --> 23:13.760
themselves by dishonest means, which should be more disreputable. Cultivate poverty like a garden

23:13.760 --> 23:22.760
herb, like sage. Do not trouble yourself much to get new things, whether clothes or friends.

23:24.260 --> 23:35.740
Turn the old, return to them. Things do not change, we change. Sell your clothes and keep

23:35.740 --> 23:44.700
your thoughts. God will see that you do not want society. If I were confined to a corner of a

23:44.700 --> 23:53.900
garret all my days like a spider, the world would be just as large to me while I had my thoughts

23:53.900 --> 24:02.760
about me. The philosopher said, From an army of three divisions one can take away its general

24:02.760 --> 24:12.780
and put it in disorder. From the man, the most abject and vulgar, one cannot take away his

24:12.780 --> 24:21.320
thought. Do not seek so anxiously to be developed, to subject yourself to many influences to be played

24:21.320 --> 24:29.540
on. It is all dissipation. Humility like darkness reveals the heavenly lights.

24:30.720 --> 24:40.720
The shadows of poverty and meanness gather around us, and low creation widens to our view.

24:42.100 --> 24:48.220
We are often reminded that if there were bestowed on us the wealth of Croesus,

24:49.400 --> 24:55.300
our aims must still be the same, and our means essentially the same.

24:56.440 --> 25:03.200
Moreover, if you are restricted in your range by poverty, if you cannot buy books and newspapers,

25:03.260 --> 25:12.460
for instance, you are but confined to the most significant and vital experiences. You are

25:12.460 --> 25:22.940
compelled to deal with the material which yields the most sugar and the most starch. It is life

25:22.940 --> 25:29.980
near the bone where it is sweetest. You are defended from being a trifler.

25:30.900 --> 25:40.400
No man loses ever on a lower level by magnanimity on a higher. Superfluous wealth can buy

25:41.120 --> 25:48.520
superfluities only. Money is not required to buy one necessary of the soul.

25:49.400 --> 25:55.900
I live in the angle of a leaden wall into whose composition was poured a little

25:55.900 --> 26:04.780
alloy of bell-metal. Often in the repose of my midday there reaches my ears a confused

26:05.540 --> 26:12.520
tintinabulum from without. It is the noise of my contemporaries. My neighbors tell me of their

26:12.520 --> 26:18.340
adventures with famous gentlemen and ladies, what notabilities they met at the dinner table,

26:18.520 --> 26:23.640
but I am no more interested in such things than in the content of the daily times.

26:25.300 --> 26:29.680
The interest and the conversation are about costume and manners,

26:30.040 --> 26:38.180
chiefly. But a goose is a goose still. Dress it as you will. They tell me of California and Texas,

26:38.240 --> 26:44.160
of England and the Indies, of the Honorable Mr. Blank, of Georgia or of Massachusetts.

26:45.120 --> 26:52.260
All transient and fleeting phenomena till I am ready to leap from their courtyard like the

26:52.260 --> 27:02.160
Mammalook Bay. I delight to come to my bearings, not walk in procession with pomp and parade in a

27:02.160 --> 27:12.660
conspicuous place, but to walk even with the builder of the universe, if I may, not to live

27:12.660 --> 27:20.760
in this restless, nervous, bustling, trivial nineteenth century, but stand or sit thoughtfully

27:20.760 --> 27:27.860
while it goes by. What are men celebrating? They are all on a committee of arrangements

27:28.420 --> 27:36.120
and hourly expect a speech from somebody. God is only the President of the day,

27:36.820 --> 27:46.440
and Webster is his orator. I love to weigh, to settle, to gravitate toward that which most

27:46.440 --> 27:53.800
strongly and rightfully attracts me, not hang by the beam of the scale and try to weigh less,

27:54.780 --> 28:03.800
not suppose a case, but take the case that is, to travel the only path I can,

28:03.800 --> 28:10.700
and that on which no power can resist me. It affords me no satisfaction

28:10.700 --> 28:16.180
to commerce, to spring an arch before I have got a solid foundation.

28:17.160 --> 28:25.160
Let us not play at kitley benders. There is a solid bottom everywhere.

28:26.260 --> 28:31.800
We read that the traveler asked the boy if the swamp before him had a hard bottom.

28:32.420 --> 28:38.560
The boy replied that it had, but presently the traveler's horse sank in up to the girths,

28:38.900 --> 28:43.200
and he observed to the boy, I thought you said this bog had a hard bottom.

28:44.040 --> 28:49.260
So it has, answered the latter, but you've not got halfway to it yet.

28:50.220 --> 28:57.720
So it is with the bogs and quicksands of society. But he is an old boy that knows it.

28:58.680 --> 29:05.640
Only what is thought, said or done, at a certain rare coincidence, is good.

29:06.740 --> 29:13.160
I would not be one of those who will foolishly drive a nail into mere lathe and plastering.

29:14.020 --> 29:21.320
Such a deed would keep me awake nights. Give me a hammer, and let me feel for the furring.

29:21.960 --> 29:31.920
Do not depend on the putty. Drive a nail home and clinch it so faithfully that you can wake

29:31.920 --> 29:37.620
up in the night and think of your work with satisfaction, a work at which you would not

29:37.620 --> 29:48.600
be ashamed to invoke the muse. So will help you God. And so only. Every nail driven should be

29:48.600 --> 29:59.820
as another rivet in the machine of the universe, you carrying on the work, rather than love,

30:00.780 --> 30:06.000
than money, than fame. Give me truth.

30:07.300 --> 30:13.820
I sat at a table where rich food and wine in abundance and obsequious attendance,

30:14.710 --> 30:22.340
but sincerity and truth were not, and I went away hungry from the inhospitable board.

30:23.860 --> 30:32.580
The hospitality was as cold as the ices. I thought that there was no need of ice to

30:32.580 --> 30:39.400
freeze them. They talked to me of the age of the wine and the fame of the vintage,

30:40.160 --> 30:48.280
but I thought of an older, a newer, and purer wine, of a more glorious vintage

30:48.840 --> 30:58.680
which they had not got, and could not buy. The style, the house and grounds, and entertainment

30:59.720 --> 31:07.300
passed for nothing with me. I called on the king, but he made me wait in his hall,

31:07.880 --> 31:15.120
and conducted like a man incapacitated for hospitality. There was a man in my neighborhood

31:15.120 --> 31:23.020
who lived in a hollow tree. His manners were truly regal. I should have done better had I called on

31:23.020 --> 31:30.900
him. How long shall we sit in our porticoes, practicing idle and musty virtues, which any

31:30.900 --> 31:38.860
work would make impertinent? As if one were to begin the day with long suffering, and hire a

31:38.860 --> 31:43.880
man to hoe his potatoes, and in the afternoon go forth to practice Christian meekness and charity

31:43.880 --> 31:54.080
with goodness aforethought, consider the china, pride, and stagnant self-complacency of mankind.

31:54.080 --> 32:01.080
And this generation inclines a little to congratulate itself on being the last of an

32:01.080 --> 32:09.240
illustrious line, and in Boston and London and Paris and Rome, thinking of its long descent,

32:10.160 --> 32:15.460
it speaks of its progress in art and science and literature with satisfaction.

32:17.340 --> 32:23.780
There are the records of the philosophical societies, and the public eulogies of great men,

32:24.620 --> 32:29.040
it is the good Adam contemplating his own virtue.

32:30.920 --> 32:37.860
Yes, we have done great deeds and sung divine songs which shall never die. That is,

32:38.260 --> 32:42.780
as long as we can remember them. The learned societies and great men of Assyria,

32:43.740 --> 32:50.360
where are they? What youthful philosophers and experimentalists we are! There is not one of my

32:50.360 --> 32:57.680
readers who has yet lived a whole human life. These may be but the spring months in the life

32:57.680 --> 33:06.180
of the race. If we have had the seven years' itch, we have not seen the seventeen-year locust yet

33:06.180 --> 33:13.840
in Concord. We are acquainted with a mere pellicle of the globe on which we live.

33:14.480 --> 33:19.580
Most have not delved six feet beneath the surface, nor leaped as many above it.

33:20.680 --> 33:29.280
We know not where we are. Beside, we are sound asleep nearly half our time,

33:30.260 --> 33:38.040
yet we esteem ourselves wise, and have an established order on the surface.

33:38.780 --> 33:45.920
Truly we are deep thinkers, we are ambitious spirits. As I stand over the insect crawling

33:45.920 --> 33:51.280
amid the pine needles on the forest floor, and endeavoring to conceal itself from my sight,

33:52.080 --> 33:57.960
and ask myself why it will cherish those humble thoughts, and bide its head from me,

33:57.980 --> 34:03.700
who might perhaps be its benefactor, and impart to its race some cheering information,

34:03.700 --> 34:12.300
I am reminded of the greater benefactor and intelligence that stands over me,

34:13.140 --> 34:18.940
the human insect. There is an incessant influx of novelty into the world,

34:19.340 --> 34:27.020
and yet we tolerate incredible dullness. I need only suggest what kind of sermons are still

34:27.020 --> 34:33.780
listened to in the most enlightened countries. There are such words as joy and sorrow,

34:34.500 --> 34:41.480
but they are only the burden of a psalm, sung with a nasal twang, while we believe

34:41.480 --> 34:48.340
in the ordinary and mean. We think that we can change our clothes only.

34:48.840 --> 34:53.440
It is said that the British Empire is very large and respectable,

34:53.960 --> 35:02.400
and the United States are a first-rate power. We do not believe that a tide rises and falls

35:02.400 --> 35:09.520
behind every man which can float the British Empire like a chip, if he should ever harbor it

35:09.520 --> 35:17.800
in his mind. Who knows what sort of seventeen-year locust will next come out of the ground.

35:18.660 --> 35:26.200
The government of the world I live in was not framed like that of Britain in after-dinner

35:26.200 --> 35:35.300
conversations over the wine. The life in us is like the water in the river. It may rise this year

35:35.300 --> 35:43.560
higher than man has ever known it, and flood the parched uplands. Even this may be the eventful

35:43.560 --> 35:50.460
year which will drown out all our muskrats. It was not always dry land where we dwell.

35:51.540 --> 35:59.020
I see far inland the banks which the stream anciently washed before science began to record

35:59.020 --> 36:06.520
its freshets. Every one has heard the story which has gone the rounds of New England of a strong and

36:06.520 --> 36:12.840
beautiful bug which came out of the dry leaf of an old table of apple-tree wood which had stood in a

36:12.840 --> 36:19.640
farmer's kitchen for sixty years, first in Connecticut and afterward in Massachusetts, from an egg

36:19.640 --> 36:27.240
deposited in the living-tree many years earlier still, as appeared by counting the annual layers

36:27.240 --> 36:35.820
beyond it, which was heard gnawing out for several weeks, hatched perchance by the heat of an urn.

36:35.820 --> 36:44.580
Who does not feel his faith in a resurrection and immortality strengthened by hearing of this?

36:45.640 --> 36:54.100
Who knows what beautiful and winged life, whose egg has been buried for ages under many concentric

36:54.100 --> 37:02.740
layers of woodenness in the dead-dry life of society, deposited at first in the alburnum

37:02.740 --> 37:10.140
of the green and living tree, which has been gradually converted into the semblance of its

37:10.140 --> 37:20.760
well-seasoned tomb, heard perchance gnawing out now for years by the astonished family of man

37:20.760 --> 37:28.680
as they sat round the festive board, may unexpectedly come forth from amidst society's

37:28.680 --> 37:38.880
most trivial and hand-celled furniture to enjoy its perfect summer life at last?

37:39.600 --> 37:48.420
I do not say that John or Jonathan will realize all this, but such is the character of that morrow

37:49.200 --> 37:58.900
which mere lapse of time can never make to dawn. The light which puts out our eyes

37:58.900 --> 38:09.260
is darkness to us. Only that day dawns to which we are awake. There is more day to dawn.

38:10.240 --> 38:14.100
The sun is but a morning star.

38:16.080 --> 38:18.400
End of Conclusion

38:20.280 --> 38:21.880
End of Walden

38:22.540 --> 38:30.860
This book, read by Gordon MacKenzie, finished July 7, 2006.

